data.name: Command_Bot_Connect_Help

data.name: Command_Bot_CreateCKL_Help
data.value: [--CreateCKL name listen_port=pooled] Starts a CD Key Lending server that others can connect to and use to logon to bnet. This will NOT allow others to learn your cd keys, but WILL allow them to logon with your keys ONCE.

data.name: Command_Bot_CreateClient_Help
data.value: [--CreateClient name=generated] Creates a new battle.net client instance.

data.name: Command_Bot_CreateAdmin_Help
data.value: [--CreateAdmin name password server_port receiver=localhost] Creates a server with an admin game and a LAN advertiser for the server.

data.name: Command_Bot_CreateServer_Help
data.value: [--CreateServer name map -options] Creates a new wc3 game server. Use help --CreateSever Options for help with options.

data.name: Command_Bot_DownloadEpicWarMap_Help
data.value: [--DownloadEpicWarMap epic_war_map_number] Downloads a map from epicwar.

data.name: Command_Bot_FindMaps_Help
data.value: [--FindMaps map_query] Returns the first five maps matching the query.

data.name: Command_Bot_GetSetting_Help
data.value: [--GetSetting setting] Returns the value of a global setting. Supported settings are tickperiod, laglimit, commandprefix.

data.name: Command_Bot_KillCKL_Help
data.value: [--KillCKL name] Kills a CD Key Lending server.

data.name: Command_Bot_KillClient_Help
data.value: [--KillClient name] Kills the named battle.net client instance.

data.name: Command_Bot_KillServer_Help
data.value: [--KillServer name] Kills the named warcraft 3 game server instance.

data.name: Command_Bot_Server_Help
data.value: [--server name command, --server main stoplistening] Forwards commands to the named warcraft 3 game server run by the bot.

data.name: Command_Bot_SetSetting_Help
data.value: [--SetSetting setting value] Sets a global setting. Supported settings are tickperiod, laglimit, commandprefix.

data.name: Command_General_Help_Help
data.value: [--help, --help command_name] Displays a list of commands, or help for a specified command.

data.name: Command_Instance_Bot_Help
data.value: [--Bot command] Forwards commands to the bot with full priviledges.

data.name: Command_Instance_Boot_Help
data.value: [--boot slot] Boots players in a slot from the game.

data.name: Command_Instance_Close_Help
data.value: [--close slot] Closes a slot, unless it contains a player.

data.name: Command_Instance_Disconnect_Help
data.value: [--disconnect] Causes the bot to disconnect from the game and attempt to pass hosting to one of the players.

data.name: Command_Instance_Freeze_Help
data.value: [--freeze slot, --freeze] Superlock. Stops players from modifying or leaving a slot or all slots.

data.name: Command_Instance_Lock_Help
data.value: [--lock slot, --lock] Stops players from leaving a slot or all slots.

data.name: Command_Instance_Open_Help
data.value: [--open slot] Opens a slot, unless it contains a player.

data.name: Command_Instance_Ping_Help
data.value: [--ping] Displays estimated latency (Round-Trip-Time) for all players.

data.name: Command_Instance_Reserve_Help
data.value: [--reserve slot player_name] Reserves a slot for a player.

data.name: Command_Instance_SetColor_Help
data.value: [--SetColor slot color] Sets a slot's color. Can't duplicate colors.

data.name: Command_Instance_SetComputer_Help
data.value: [--CPU slot [difficulty]] Places a computer in a slot, unless it contains a player.

data.name: Command_Instance_SetHandicap_Help
data.value: [--SetHandicap slot handicap] Sets a slot's handicap. Only allows 50,60,70,80,90,100.

data.name: Command_Instance_SetTeams_Help
data.value: [--SetTeams 3v3, --SetTeams 2v2v2] Opens and closes slots based on team sizes.

data.name: Command_Instance_SetTeam_Help
data.value: [--SetTeam slot team] Sets a slot's team.

data.name: Command_Instance_Swap_Help
data.value: [--swap slot1 slot2] Swaps the contents of two slots.

data.name: Command_Instance_Unlock_Help
data.value: [--unlock slot, --unlock] Enables players to leave and modify a slot or all slots.

data.name: Command_Client_Host_ExtraHelp
data.value: Options=[*] Admin=-Admin=Strilanc,-a=user,-a: Sets the auto-elevated username. Use no argument to match your name. Autostart=-Autostart, -as: Instances will start automatically when they fill up. Instances=-Instances=X, -i=X: Sets the initial number of instances. Use =0 for unlimited instances. FullShare=-FullShare: Turns on wc3's 'full shared control' option. Grab=-Grab: Downloads the map file from joining players. LoadInGame=-LoadInGame, -lig: Players wait for loaders in the game. Nicer than staring, but not compatible with some maps (causes desyncs). MultiObs=-MultiObs,-mo: Turns on observers, and creates a special slot which can accept large amounts of players. The map must have two available obs slots for this to work. NoUL=-NoUL: Turns off uploads from the bot, but still allows players to download from each other. NoDL=-NoDL: Boots players who need to DL the map. Obs=-Obs, -o: Turns on full observers. ObsOnDefeat=-ObsOnDefeat, -od: Turns on observers on defeat. Permanent=-Permanent, -perm: Automatically recreate closed instances and automatically advertises when new instances are available. Private=-Private, -p: Advertises the game as private instead of public. RandomHero=-RandomHero, -rh: Turns on the wc3 'random hero' option. RandomRace=-RandomRace, -rr: Turns on the wc3 'random race' option. Referees=-Referees,-ref: Turns on observer referees. Reserve=-Reserve=Name, -r: Reserves the first available slot for the player with the given name. Omit =Name to match your name. Speed=-Speed=X: Changes default speed. Possible values for X are medium/slow. Teams=-Teams=XvX, -t=XvXvX: Sets the initial number of open slots for each team. TeamsApart=-TeamsApart: Turns off wc3's 'teams together' option. UnlockTeams=-UnlockTeams: Turns off wc3's 'lock teams' option. Visibility=-Visibility=X, -vis=X: Changes the default visibility option from map default. Possible values of X are All/Explored/None.

data.name: Command_Client_AdLink_Help
data.value: [--AdLink other_client_name] Causes the other client to advertise the same games as this client. Note: If either client fails to advertise, they both fail.

data.name: Command_Client_AdUnlink_Help
data.value: [AdUnlink other_client_name] Causes the other client to no longer advertise the same games as this client.

data.name: Command_Client_GetPort_Help
data.value: [GetPort] Returns the listen port reported to bnet.

data.name: Command_Client_SetPort_Help
data.value: [SetPort] Changes listen port reported to bnet.

data.name: Command_Instance_Elevate_Help
data.value: [Elevate password] Gives access to admin commands.

data.name: Command_Client_AddUser_Help
data.value: [--AddUser name] Adds a new user with the default new user permissions.

data.name: Command_Client_Elevate_Help
data.value: [Elevate, Elevate username] Elevates you or a specified user to admin in your hosted game.

data.name: Command_Instance_VoteStart_Help
data.value: [VoteStart, VoteStart cancel] Votes to start the game. Only works in autostarted games. Requires at least 2 players and at least a 2/3 majority.

data.name: Command_Client_Connect_Help
data.value: [Connect Hostname] Connects to a battle.net server at the given address.

data.name: Command_Client_Say_Help
data.value: [Say text] Makes the bot say stuff, including bnet commands.

data.name: Command_Client_StartAdvertising_Help
data.value: [StartAdvertising game_name map_query ...options] Adds an entry to the bnet games list. The only option is -private / -p.

data.name: Command_Client_StopAdvertising_Help
data.value: [StopAdvertising] Removes any entry in the bnet games list. Also unlinks any linked servers.

data.name: Command_Bot_CreateLan_Help
data.value: [CreateLan name server_port receiver=localhost] Creates a lan advertiser.
